{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[{"debug":1},true],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"zotero":1,"inscriptions":7,"isBulletin":239},{"title":2,"author":3,"date":4,"citation":5,"uri":6},"Aurelius Samohil between ius and identity","Giuffrida","2020","\u003Cspan>Claudia Giuffrida, ‘Aurelius Samohil between Ius and Identity’, \u003Ci>Codex. Giornale Romanistico Di Studi Giuridici Politici e Sociali\u003C/i> 1 (2020): 59–88\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/KISJUYBW",[8,132],{"file":9,"uri":9,"title":10,"status":11,"editionAuthor":13,"type":14,"objectType":18,"material":22,"condition":26,"layoutDesc":28,"handNote":37,"date":53,"places":57,"geo":66,"provenance":59,"provenanceGeo":70,"country":73,"region":74,"settlement":75,"repository":76,"idno":80,"textLang":83,"tmNumber":87,"facsimile":88,"letterHeights":95,"publications":99,"zotero":106,"keywords":113,"html":124,"bibl":125,"bulletinDateSort":131,"citedRangeSort":126,"languageSort":84,"materialSort":23,"typeSort":15},"ISic000794","Funerary inscription for Kale",{"_":12},"draft",null,{"_":15,"ana":16,"ref":17},"funerary","#function.funerary","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/92.html",{"_":19,"ana":20,"ref":21},"plaque","#object.plaque","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259",{"_":23,"ana":24,"ref":25},"marble","#material.stone.marble","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html",{"ana":27},"#condition.complete",{"layout":29},{"p":30,"rs":31,"damage":35},"Four lines of ancient Greek filling the upper portion of the face of the stone, with a consistent left margin, the right side more cramped and irregular. The lower part of the stone is blank.",{"_":32,"ana":33,"ref":34},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"ana":36},"#text_condition.complete #text_condition.legible",{"lettering":38,"dimensions":39},"Letters are somewhat irregular in size, with simple straight line serifs terminating most strokes. Alpha with both broken bar and straight bar; beta both open and closed with rounded eyes; epsilon quadrate with equal length strokes; theta and omicron are rhomboid; kappa has short arms; mu has vertical first and last, short middle strokes; pi has overhanging horizontal; sigma is quadrate lunate; omega is inverted cursive form, having the appearance of mu; the pi-rho ligature is used twice; staurogram at the end of the text.",[40,49],{"type":41,"l":42,"from":43,"to":44,"h":45,"unit":46,"atLeast":47,"atMost":48},"letterHeight","Line 1-4","line1","line4","30-45","mm","30","45",{"type":50,"l":51,"from":43,"to":52,"unit":46},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2","line2",{"_":54,"notBefore":55,"notAfter":56},"4th — 5th century CE",301,500,[58,62],{"_":59,"type":60,"ref":61},"Centuripae","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462153",{"_":63,"type":64,"ref":65},"Centuripe","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2525032",[67],[68,69],37.62336,14.74049,[71,72],37.614275,14.733503,"Italy","Sicily","Palermo",{"_":77,"role":78,"ref":79},"Museo Archeologico Regionale Antonino Salinas","museum","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/064",{"_":81,"type":82},"8707","inventory",{"_":84,"mainLang":85,"languages":86},"Ancient Greek","grc",[84],"493900",{"n":89,"url":90,"height":91,"width":92,"desc":93,"surfaceType":94},"screen","ISic000794_tiled.tif","3680px","5520px","Photo J.Prag 2022-05-23","front",[96],{"atLeast":97,"atMost":98},30,45,[100,101,102,103,104,105],"Supplementum epigraphicum graecum, 1923-","L'année épigraphique: revue des publications épigraphiques relatives a l'antiquité romaine., 1888-","Manni Piraino, 1973, IGMusPalermo","Notizie degli scavi di antichità, 1876-","Ferrua, 1989, Note e giunte alle iscrizioni cristiane antiche della Sicilia","Giuffrida, 2020, Aurelius Samohil between ius and identity",[107,108,109,110,111,112],"F2GG87EQ","R46KDTZX","F66S4X3M","4MCP2PVV","759ZXHKQ","KISJUYBW",[114,115,116,15,19,23,117,118,119,120,121,122,123,85],"isic000794","funerary inscription for kale",{"_":12},"centuripae","centuripe","italy","sicily","palermo","museo archeologico regionale antonino salinas","ancient greek","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ἐνθάδε κῖτε · \u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"#attested\" data-text=\"Καλὴ\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Καλὴ\">Καλὴ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">π͡ρ̣\u003C/span>ε(σ)β(ῦτις) \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ζήσ(ασ)α · ἔτη · \u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">ν\u003C/span>´ ἀμέπτ\u003Cspan class=\"inverted\" title=\"inverted: ω\">((ω))\u003C/span>ς \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>τὸν βίον τελ(ευτᾷ) τῇ πρ(ὸ) \u003Cspan class=\"supraline\" title=\"line above\">ιθ\u003C/span>´ κ(αλα)ν(δῶν) \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>Ὀκτ\u003Cspan class=\"inverted\" title=\"inverted: ω\">((ω))\u003C/span>βρί\u003Cspan class=\"inverted\" title=\"inverted: ω\">((ω))\u003C/span>ν 𐆠 \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">l.2 reg., orig. ἀμέπτως\u003C/p>",{"author":3,"date":4,"citedRange":126,"ptr":127,"ref":129,"inscriptionDate":4,"title":2,"citation":5,"uri":6},"60-61",{"target":128},"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/KISJUYBW",{"_":130,"target":130},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002323",2020,{"file":133,"uri":133,"title":134,"status":135,"editionAuthor":13,"type":136,"objectType":137,"material":139,"condition":141,"layoutDesc":142,"handNote":148,"date":164,"places":168,"geo":175,"provenance":170,"provenanceGeo":179,"country":73,"region":74,"settlement":173,"repository":182,"idno":185,"textLang":187,"tmNumber":194,"facsimile":195,"letterHeights":200,"publications":207,"zotero":216,"keywords":225,"html":233,"bibl":234,"bulletinDateSort":131,"citedRangeSort":235,"languageSort":238,"materialSort":140,"typeSort":15},"ISic000781","Funerary inscription of Aurelius Samohil",{"_":12},{"_":15,"ana":16,"ref":17},{"_":19,"ana":20,"ref":138},"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259.html",{"_":140,"ana":24,"ref":25},"marble (white)",{"ana":27},{"layout":143},{"p":144,"rs":145,"damage":146},"A single line of Hebrew is followed by 14 lines of Latin; the Latin text observes a more or less regular left margin, irregular on the right. The lower right and left corners contain small incised menorahs, with the last line of text between them consisting simply of 'overspill' from the preceding line, offset towards the right.",{"_":32,"ana":33,"ref":34},{"ana":147},"#text_condition.legible",{"lettering":149,"dimensions":150},"Letters generally neatly and regularly cut, with basic serifs on the long strokes. B is somewhat irregular in fomration, sometimes with equal loops, sometimes with smaller upper loop; C is large and open; E is narrow, with three short equal horizontal strokes; G has distinctive form of small C with a tail descending to lower right; M is formed of four equal diagonal strokes; P has a somewhat elongated frequently (but not always) closed loop, but some instances have a wide horizaontal foot also; Q is closed with a trailing tail;  R is usually closed, with a tail usually straight and extended but finishing above the line; S is frequently oversize. The two menorahs at the foot of the inscription are 15 mm and 23 mm (the left is incomplete).",[151,156,162],{"type":41,"l":152,"from":43,"to":43,"h":153,"unit":46,"atLeast":154,"atMost":155},"Line 1","7-15","7","15",{"type":41,"l":157,"from":52,"to":158,"h":159,"unit":46,"atLeast":160,"atMost":161},"Lines 2-15","line15","9-19","9","19",{"type":50,"l":51,"from":43,"to":52,"h":163,"unit":46},"not measured",{"_":165,"notBefore":166,"notAfter":166,"evidence":167},"383 CE",383,"internal-date",[169,172],{"_":170,"type":60,"ref":171},"Catina","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462270",{"_":173,"type":64,"ref":174},"Catania","http://sws.geonames.org/2525068",[176],[177,178],37.49223,15.07041,[180,181],37.505019,15.088801,{"_":183,"role":78,"ref":184},"Museo Civico di Catania","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/018",{"_":186,"type":82},"540",{"_":188,"mainLang":189,"otherLangs":190,"languages":191},"Latin and Hebrew","la","heb",[192,193],"Latin","Hebrew","175684",{"n":89,"url":196,"height":197,"width":198,"desc":199,"surfaceType":94},"ISic000781_tiled.tif","2856px","4272px","Photo by students of Liceo Lazzaro, 2017-05-11",[201,204],{"atLeast":202,"atMost":203},7,15,{"atLeast":205,"atMost":206},9,19,[101,100,100,208,209,210,211,212,213,214,215,105],"Korhonen, 2004, IMusCatania","Libertini, 1929, Epigrafe giudaico-latina rinvenuta in Catania","Frey, 1936-1952, CIJ","Wilson, 1990, Sicily under the Roman Empire: the archaeology of a Roman province, 36 B.C. - A.D. 535","Manganaro, 1993, Greco nei pagi e latino nelle città della Sicilia romana tra I e VI sec. d.C.","Noy, 1993, Jewish inscriptions of Western Europe","Grüll, 2000, \" Conquerors, Patriarchs and the Law of the Lord\". Interpretation of a late antique Jewish epitaph","Manganaro, 2004-2005, Giudei grecanici nella Sicilia di eta imperale (documentazione epigrafica e figurativa)",[108,107,107,217,218,219,220,221,222,223,224,112],"2EUC82DH","Q7I7M6C5","ACIZXQF2","VF9MMBI9","JBI7CI5R","IBA4JMAN","ZCRPNPUD","BMHLMJAM",[226,227,228,15,19,140,229,230,119,120,230,231,232,189],"isic000781","funerary inscription of aurelius samohil",{"_":12},"catina","catania","museo civico di catania","latin and hebrew","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"heb\">Š[LW]M ῾L YŚR᾿L ᾿MN ᾿MN ŠLWM ŠMW᾿L\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr